+# Project Journal Guidelines
+
+## Overview
+
+The project journal serves as a continuous record of the project's progress, decisions, challenges, and solutions. It provides valuable context for all stakeholders and creates a historical record of the project's evolution.
+
+## Journal Structure
+
+### 1. Entry Organization
+
+- Create a new journal entry for each significant work session
+- Store entries in a chronological directory structure:
+  ```
+  /journal
+  ├── entries/
+  │   ├── YYYY-MM-DD-title.md
+  │   ├── YYYY-MM-DD-title.md
+  │   └── ...
+  └── index.md  # Overview and entry index
+  ```
+- Name files with date prefix for easy chronological sorting
+
+### 2. Entry Content
+
+Each journal entry should include:
+
+- **Header**: Date, time, and entry title
+- **Goals**: Objectives for the current work session
+- **Progress**: Accomplishments and advancements
+- **Challenges**: Problems encountered and solutions implemented
+- **Decisions**: Key choices made and their rationale
+- **Next Steps**: Planned activities for the next session
+- **Resources**: Links to relevant documentation, research, or references
+
+## Implementation Requirements
+
+### 1. Entry Creation
+
+- Create a new entry at the start of each significant work session
+- Always verify the current date and time using the terminal:
+  ```bash
+  date "+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S"
+  ```
+- Use the verified date in the entry header and filename
+
+### 2. Entry Template
+
+```markdown
+# Journal Entry: [Title]
+
+**Date**: YYYY-MM-DD
+**Time**: HH:MM:SS
+**Duration**: [Approximate work session length]
+
+## Goals
+- [Goal 1]
+- [Goal 2]
+- ...
+
+## Progress
+- [Accomplishment 1]
+- [Accomplishment 2]
+- ...
+
+## Challenges & Solutions
+- **Challenge**: [Description]
+  - **Solution**: [Approach taken]
+- **Challenge**: [Description]
+  - **Solution**: [Approach taken]
+- ...
+
+## Key Decisions
+- [Decision 1]: [Rationale]
+- [Decision 2]: [Rationale]
+- ...
+
+## Observations
+- [Insight or observation]
+- ...
+
+## Next Steps
+- [Next task 1]
+- [Next task 2]
+- ...
+
+## Resources
+- [Link to relevant documentation, research, code, etc.]
+- ...
+```
+
+### 3. Maintenance Procedures
+
+- Update the journal index with each new entry
+- Reference specific commits, files, or documentation when relevant
+- Include code snippets, terminal output, or screenshots as needed
+- Cross-reference journal entries with project plan tasks
+
+### 4. Best Practices
+
+- Be concise but thorough
+- Focus on meaningful insights and progress, not routine activities
+- Document the reasoning behind decisions, not just the decisions themselves
+- Capture unexpected behaviors, unusual solutions, and lessons learned
+- Maintain professional tone and clarity
+
+## Integration with Project Workflow
+
+- Review previous journal entries before starting new work sessions
+- Reference journal entries in commit messages when applicable
+- Use journal entries to inform project status reports
+- Include journal review in milestone completion checklist
+
+Remember to always verify the current date and time before creating a new journal entry to ensure accuracy in the project timeline.
